  <h1>LG Dryer Not Heating Repair Service Los Angeles County</h1>
  <p>When your LG dryer tumbles but produces no heat, you're looking at a heating element, thermal fuse, or gas valve issue that needs immediate professional attention. Our techs fix 85% of heating problems on the first visit across Burbank, Pasadena, and throughout LA County.</p>

<h2>Warning Signs Your LG Dryer Heating System Failed</h2>
<p>The most obvious sign is clothes coming out damp after a full cycle, but our techs see several other symptoms that indicate heating failure. If your LG DLEX or DLGX series dryer runs for the full cycle time but everything feels room temperature, the heating element likely burned out. We also get calls when the dryer starts normally but shuts off after 10-15 minutes - this usually points to a tripped thermal fuse protecting the heating circuit.</p>
<figure class="article-img">
  <img src="/images/symptoms/lg-dryer-not-heating-wet-clothes-new.webp"
       alt="Wet damp clothes pulled from LG dryer after full cycle — no heat symptom"
       width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" />
  <figcaption>Full cycle, drum spinning normally — clothes still wet.
  Classic no-heat symptom pointing to heating element or thermal fuse</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>Gas LG dryers show different symptoms when the igniter or gas valve fails. You might smell a brief gas odor at startup that disappears, or hear the igniter clicking repeatedly without the whoosh of gas lighting. Electric models with failed heating elements often trip the home's circuit breaker, especially in older homes around Beverly Hills and Santa Monica with aging electrical panels.</p>
<p>Don't wait if you notice these symptoms - continued operation without heat can damage other components. Nine times out of ten, we catch heating problems before they cascade into more expensive repairs like <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-drum-roller-replacement/">drum roller damage</a> from extended runtime.</p>
<h2>Our LG Dryer Heating Repair Process</h2>
<p>When you call (323) 990-7550, we'll schedule your same-day appointment and our tech arrives with a fully stocked van containing the most common LG heating components. The first thing we check is power supply and circuit breakers, then move to the thermal fuse location behind the exhaust vent - this $15 part causes 40% of heating failures.</p>
<figure class="article-img article-img--square">
  <img src="/images/symptoms/lg-dryer-not-heating-thermal-fuse-new.webp"
       alt="LG dryer thermal fuse — small part that causes 40% of no-heat failures"
       width="600" height="600" loading="lazy" />
  <figcaption>The thermal fuse — costs $15, causes 40% of LG dryer
  no-heat calls. Blows once and won't reset</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>For electric models, we test the heating element with a multimeter, checking both continuity and proper resistance values.</p>
<figure class="article-img">
  <img src="/images/symptoms/lg-dryer-not-heating-multimeter-new.webp"
       alt="Technician testing LG dryer heating element with multimeter"
       width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" />
  <figcaption>Multimeter test on the heating element —
  8-12 ohms is normal, open circuit means the element has failed</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>LG heating elements typically read 8-12 ohms when functioning correctly. If the element tests bad, we show you the exact part cost on our supplier website before proceeding with <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-heating-element-replacement/">heating element replacement</a>.</p>
<p>Gas dryer diagnosis involves checking the igniter, gas valve coils, and flame sensor. Our techs carry igniter assemblies for DLGX3001 and newer models, since these fail predictably after 8-10 years. We complete most heating repairs within 45 minutes, test the unit through a full heated cycle, and provide you with operating instructions specific to your model.</p>
<h3>Same-Day Diagnostic Guarantee</h3>
<p>Our technicians diagnose heating problems on the spot using professional test equipment, not guesswork. We carry thermal imaging cameras to spot heat distribution issues and multimeters calibrated for appliance voltage testing. The diagnostic fee gets waived when you proceed with our repair, and we provide a detailed explanation of what failed and why.</p>
<h2>Why Professional Repair Beats DIY for LG Heating Issues</h2>
<p>Heating system repairs involve high-voltage electrical connections and gas line safety that require proper training. Our techs see dozens of DIY disasters every month, from crossed wires that damage control boards to improperly seated <a href="/repairs/lg-dryer-thermal-fuse-replacement/">thermal fuse replacements</a> that create fire hazards.</p>
<p>The biggest DIY mistake is replacing the thermal fuse without addressing what caused it to blow. That $15 fuse protects your home from dryer fires, and it trips for specific reasons - blocked vents, failed heating elements, or restricted airflow. Simply swapping the fuse means it'll blow again within days, often damaging other components.</p>
<figure class="article-img">
  <img src="/images/symptoms/lg-dryer-not-heating-vent-clog-new.webp"
       alt="Clogged dryer exhaust vent — primary cause of thermal fuse failure"
       width="800" height="600" loading="lazy" />
  <figcaption>Blocked vent causes heat buildup that blows the thermal fuse —
  replace the fuse without clearing this and it blows again within days</figcaption>
</figure>
<p>Our repair process includes checking exhaust airflow, cleaning internal lint buildup, and testing all safety circuits. We use OEM parts only, source them transparently so you can verify pricing, and back everything with a 1-year warranty on both parts and labor. DIY repairs void manufacturer warranties and often cost more when the job needs professional correction.</p>
<h3>Safety and Code Compliance</h3>
<p>Gas dryer repairs must meet California safety codes, especially in older Glendale and Torrance neighborhoods with vintage gas lines. Our techs are Bureau of Household Goods licensed (#49573) and carry proper insurance for gas appliance work. Electric dryer heating elements operate at 240 volts - enough to cause serious injury without proper safety procedures.</p>
<h2>LG Dryer Heating Repair Cost Breakdown</h2>
<p>Most LG heating repairs range from $320-380 including parts and labor, significantly less than replacing your dryer. Electric heating elements cost $45-85 depending on your model, while thermal fuses run $12-25. Gas dryer igniters typically cost $35-65, and gas valve assemblies range from $85-140.

Labor accounts for roughly half the total cost, reflecting the technical skill required for safe heating system work. Complex jobs requiring dryer removal or special access tools may reach $350-450, but this still beats purchasing a new LG dryer at $800-1500.

About half our service calls end up being simple fixes - loose connections, error code resets, or minor adjustments that cost just the service call fee of $65-120. Our flexible pricing policy means if we source parts from our warehouse stock purchased at better prices, we pass those savings directly to you. Returning customers receive a 10% labor discount, and the exact quote is always provided on-site after diagnosis.</p>
<h3>Transparent Parts Pricing</h3>
<p>We show you the exact part cost on supplier websites before ordering, so there are no surprises. OEM LG parts carry manufacturer warranties and maintain your dryer's efficiency ratings. Generic parts might cost less upfront but often fail prematurely, leading to repeat service calls and voided warranties.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<h3>How long does LG dryer heating element replacement take?</h3>
<p>Most heating element replacements take 30-45 minutes once we access the rear panel. We test the new element through a complete heated cycle before leaving. Some models require removing the drum for access, which adds 15-20 minutes.</p>
<h3>Why did my LG dryer thermal fuse blow?</h3>
<p>Thermal fuses blow from excessive heat caused by restricted airflow, failed heating elements, or blocked exhaust vents. Simply replacing the fuse without fixing the underlying cause means it will blow again. Our techs always diagnose what caused the fuse failure.</p>
<h3>Can I use my LG dryer if it's not heating?</h3>
<p>You can use air-dry or fluff cycles safely, but avoid heated cycles until repair. Running heat cycles with a failed heating element can damage other components or trip safety circuits repeatedly.</p>
<h3>How do I know if my LG gas dryer igniter is bad?</h3>
<p>A failing igniter glows dimly orange instead of bright white, takes longer than 90 seconds to light, or clicks repeatedly without igniting gas. The igniter should glow bright white and ignite gas within 45-60 seconds.</p>
<h3>Do you repair all LG dryer models in Los Angeles?</h3>
<p>We service all LG electric and gas dryer models including DLEX, DLGX, and DLE series throughout LA County. Our vans carry parts for the most common models, with next-day availability for specialty components. Call (323) 990-7550 for model-specific information.</p>

